Quickly adding lines with `nl` utility

If you ever need to add numbering alongside a file than `nl` is the tool for you:
```
$ head dirs.txt | nl
     1	totali
     2	./dirB/dirF/dirG
     3	./dirB/dirF
     4	./dirB/dirF
     5	./dirB
     6	.
     7	.
     8	./dirA/dirC/dirD
     9	./dirA/dirC/dirD
    10	./dirA/dirC/dirD
```